  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready, skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary, and if you like your steak well-done, it may take you a little longer than 10 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/steak-with-charred-corn-rice-and-spicy-mayo/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a dry, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Heat a separate dry, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Pat your <strong>rump steak[s]</strong> dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen<strong> </strong>paper, drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season all over with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/steak-with-charred-corn-rice-and-spicy-mayo/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once very hot, add the <strong>seasoned</strong> <strong>steak</strong> to one of the pans</p><p>For rare, cook for 2 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 2-3 min on each side; for medium, cook for 3-4 min on each side</p><p>Once the steak is cooked, transfer to a plate to rest</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/steak-with-charred-corn-rice-and-spicy-mayo/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the steak is cooking, add a generous knob of <strong>butter</strong> to the other pan</p><p>Drain your<strong> sweetcorn</strong></p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>drained sweetcorn</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until golden brown – this is your <strong>charred buttery corn</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/steak-with-charred-corn-rice-and-spicy-mayo/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> mayo</strong>, <strong>sriracha</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>red chilli relish</strong> in a bowl – this is your <strong>spicy mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/steak-with-charred-corn-rice-and-spicy-mayo/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cooked white long grain rice</strong> to the buttery corn and cook for 2-3 min further or until warmed through – this is your<strong> charred corn rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/steak-with-charred-corn-rice-and-spicy-mayo/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>vinaigrette</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen<strong> </strong>paper</p><p>On a clean board, slice the <strong>rested steak</strong> into strips</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/steak-with-charred-corn-rice-and-spicy-mayo/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> sliced steak </strong>with the<strong> charred corn rice </strong>and<strong> salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle the<strong> spicy mayo</strong> over the<strong> </strong>steak and the<strong> vinaigrette</strong> over the salad</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
